VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ad disguised as a room layout. A single hotel room is divided into four quadrants: winter, spring, summer, autumn. The tagline, the weather checked in before you did, lands on the floor.'

[16:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Idog manages to combine set design, interior layout, and advertising copy in one image. Finally, we return to transit with skyline routes and ocean line. These floating and underwater transit maps have station names, route lines,'

[16:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and legends that all make sense. The islands and aquatic habitats feel like part of the same world. Idog\'s ability to produce usable transit diagrams within fantastical settings underscores the model\'s understanding of both'

[16:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'graphic design and world building. You\'ve just seen what Ideogram 4.0 can generate. Let\'s see how the workflow actually works. Before anything else, make sure to update Comfy UI to avoid crashes and ensure compatibility. You'

[16:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can get the default Comfy UI ideoggram 4.0 workflow by going to templates. Here I made some tweaks to this to make it run more easily on low VRAMm setups. I replaced the default text encoder with a'

[17:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lighter Q4KM GGUF encoder and swapped to KJ diffusion loader nodes which gives better control on Blackwell and ADA Love Lace GPUs. But if you have an older gen GPU, it\'s best to use the default'

[17:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'settings. Now this is important. The model doesn\'t support Sage Attention, so make sure it is disabled. I\'ve tried using the GGUFS, and they were painfully slow. When using the FP8s to generate a 2 megapixel default preset image, it'

[17:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'usually takes 4 to 5 minutes, but with GGUFS, it takes twice the time. So, I strongly recommend FP8s if you have 8 gigs of VRAM paired with 32 gigs of system RAM. Only use the GGUFS if you'

[17:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have 16 GB of system RAM. Also, if you\'re going to use GGUFS and run into an issue, you don\'t have to panic. There is an easy fix. The standard Comfy UI GGUF custom node by City96 hasn\'t'

[17:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'officially merged the architecture support for Ideog 4 just yet. Since the official City96 repository is still waiting for the pull request to be merged, the community has already jumped'

[18:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in and patched it. You just need to swap out your current GGUF node directory for a patched community fork that has the Ideogram 4 architecture hard-coded in. Navigate to your Comfy UI custom nodes directory on your drive. Delete the'

[18:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'existing Comfy UI GGUF folder. Open your command prompt or terminal inside the custom nodes folder and clone the working community fork by running this exact command. Restart Comfy UI. Load up your workflow and now you\'ll be able to'

[18:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'run the GGUF models as usual. Here you have links to all the models you need. Since I\'m running on a low VRAMm setup, I prefer only using the main text encoder, which is Quen 3 VL8B. To enhance your prompts, you can use a'

[18:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'local LLM running on LM Studio or a cloud model like Gemini or Chat GPT. The resolution selector may look simple, but it decides the shape of your canvas before you even start prompting. Aspect ratio gives you the frame square for'

[19:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'balanced compositions, portrait for posters or phone wallpapers, 16 to9 for YouTube visuals, and ultrawide for panoramic worlds. The official workflow defaults to 1.0 megapixel, which is fine for testing, but I always lean toward'

[19:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '2.0 megapixels because it provides more room for labels, diagrams, and tiny details. IOG 4 offers three presets: quality, default, and turbo. Quality runs the highest number of steps and can'

[19:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'produce polished results, but in my testing, default often feels cleaner. Quality sometimes adds unwanted micro labels or gibberish and textheavy images. Default renders faster and still looks great, making it my preferred'

[19:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'balance for posters, infographics, and diagrams. Turbo is perfect for quick idea exploration. And once I like the concept, I switch to default for a cleaner version on my system. With a Blackwell RTX 5068 GB, a 2 megapixel'

[19:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'default render takes about 4 to 5 minutes using FP8 models. Idog 4 can generate images from a simple sentence, but its true strength appears when using structured prompts. You don\'t need to'

[20:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'handwrite giant JSON files. There is a template attached in the workflow for your reference, and it makes things so much more convenient. It acts like a translator. You describe your idea normally and specify the aspect ratio.'

[20:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Then a local or cloud LLM converts it into structured JSON file. Your support means absolutely everything to me. It\'s what allows me to grow this channel and keep delivering these free low VRAMm'

[20:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'optimized workflows and guides to you guys. If you found this tutorial helpful, smash that subscribe button, leave a thumbs up, and drop your thoughts in the comments.'
